<item>
            <title>[SOLR-16971] RealTimeGet with Composite router throws NPE</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16971</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;RealTimeGet with Composite router throws NPE at slice resolution time making it unusable.&lt;br/&gt;
I would like to add a check and possibly return nothing instead of the NPE.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[c:content s:shard1 r:core_node3 x:content_shard1_replica_n1] 
o.a.s.h.RequestHandlerBase java.lang.NullPointerException: 
Cannot invoke &quot;org.apache.solr.common.cloud.Slice.getName()&quot; because &quot;slice&quot; is null =&amp;gt; 
java.lang.NullPointerException: Cannot invoke &quot;org.apache.solr.common.cloud.Slice.getName()&quot; because &quot;slice&quot; is null
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;one workaround is to pass &quot;&lt;em&gt;route&lt;/em&gt;&quot;&#160;param.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
